NAME
	playeraccess - manage the access-list of the player tool

SYNOPSIS
	playeraccess a[dd] <name>
	playeraccess [l[ist]]
	playeraccess r[emove] <name>

ACCESS CLASS
	Every wizard may use 'list', but 'add' and 'remove' are restricted
	to arches and keepers.

DESCRIPTION
	This command can be used to list the people who are allowed to use
	the player tool, to add new people to the list or to remove people
	from the list.

ARGUMENTS
	<name>	the name of the wizard to grand/revoke access
	<none>	same as 'l[ist]'

SEE ALSO
	playerget, playerput
